<h1>Events</h1>
<img class="divider" src="/img/divider.png" alt="">
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">8 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>13th Maldon Beer &amp; Cider Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>8-11 April. 55+ real ales, inc selection from London micros. Plus cider, perry and fruit wines. Belgian beer bar.Hot, food, snacks, live music. Wed 4-11pm, Thurs-Sat 11-1. Entry &pound;1, CAMRA members free. Wheelchair access</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Plume School, Farnbridge Rd, Maldon, Essex<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 08.04.15, 10.00am</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">9 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>4th Isle Of Man Beer &amp; Cider Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>9-11 April. 125+ real ales, 20+ ciders and perries. Hot food/snacks. Live music Fri/Sat. Thur 5-11pm, &pound;5, Fri 12-5pm, &pound;5, 5-11, &pound;7. Sat 12 noon-11pm, &pound;5. CAMRA members free.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Villa Marina Complex, Harris Promenade, Douglas<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 09.04.15, 10.00am</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">9 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>Doncaster&#039;s 25th Beer Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>9-11 April. 110 real ales, ciders and foreign beer bar. Thur 5-11pm, Fri/Sat 11-11. Food until 9.30pm. Entertainment Fri&#039;Sat eves.&pound;4-6. CAMRA members free.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Hub, Chappell Drive<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 09.04.15, 11.00am</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">9 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>Bolton Beer Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>9-11 April. 40+ real ales, cider, perry and Ukrainian craft beer. Thur 4-10.30pm, Fri/Sat  12 noon-10pm, &pound;2, Fri &pound;3 after 5.30pm. CAMRA members free entry Thur, &pound;1 all other sessions.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Bolton Ukrainian Club, 99 Castle Street (10 mins walk from train station) 471 &amp; 510 bus routes<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 09.04.15, 11.00am</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">9 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>Walsall Real Ale And Cider  Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>9-11 April. 100+ real ales, ciders and perries.Thurd 4-11pm, Fr/Sat 12 noon-11pm</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Walsall Town Hall, Leicester Street<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 09.04.15, 11.00am</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">10 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>High Peak &amp; NE Cheshire 6th New Mills Beer Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>10-11 April.  Fri/Sat 12 noon-11pm. Free admission.  approx 25 beers, plus cider and hot food. 5 mins from New Mills station.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Chalkers Snooker Club, Newtown, New Mills, Derbyshire<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 10.04.15, 12.00pm</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">10 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>37th Bath Beer Festival</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>10-11 April. Fri 6-11pm, Sat 11am-3.30pm, 6-11pm. 35 real ales plus ciders and perries. &pound;8 all sessions inc &pound;2 beer tokens and souvenir glass. Further &pound;2 tokens for CAMRA members.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Bath Rugby Club, Premier Suite, Recreation Ground, off Pulteney Mews, 10 min walk from Bath Spa rail station<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 10.04.15, 12.00pm</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">10 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>4th Guisborough Charity Beer Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>10-11 April. 36 real ales mainly from West Yorks, Durham and Northumberland, plus ciders, perries and fruit wines. Tombola. Fri/Sat 11am-4pm, Fri/Sat 6-11pm. &pound;5. CAMRA members &pound;1 refundable.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Guisborough Parish Hall, Bow Street<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 10.04.15, 12.00pm</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">15 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>Stourbridge Beer Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>15-18 April.  90+ real ales, ciders and perries. Wed 7-10pm, members night and VIPs only. Thur 7-11pm, Fri 12 noon-11pm, Sat 12 noon-9pm or when beer runs out. Hot/cold food. Thur/Fri &pound;3, &pound;2 beer tokens for CAMRA members. Sat free. No music -- just beer and chat.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Town Hall, Crown Centre, Stourbridge, West Midlands 5 mins from Stourbridge Town station &amp; bus interchange<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 15.04.15, 12.00pm</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="sub_hero event">
<span class="badge">15 Apr 2015</span>
<h3>39th Newcastle Beer &amp; Cider Fest</h3>
<div class="snippet">
<div class="text wide">
<p>15-16 April. Wed 6-10.30pm, Thur/Fri 12 noon-10.30pm. Sat 12 noon-5pm. &pound;5, CAMRA members free. Hot/cold food. Entertainment Sat eve.</p>
<p><strong>Venue:</strong> Students Union, Northumbria University,, Sandyford Rd, Newcastle upon Tyne<br><strong>Date/time:</strong> 15.04.15, 12.00pm</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
